#) Can you explain about try with resources?
#) How does try with resources work?

try-with-resources is a feature introduced in Java 7 that makes
 it easy to automatically close resources (like files, connections, streams, etc.) after use â€” without needing a finally block.


 #)Try-with-resources ensures that resources like files, DB connections, streams are automatically closed after use, without needing a finally block.
#)It works only with classes that implement AutoCloseable.


import java.io.FileReader;
import java.io.IOException;

public class TryWithResourceExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        try (FileReader fr = new FileReader("test.txt")) {
            int ch;
            while ((ch = fr.read()) != -1) {
                System.out.print((char) ch);
            }
        } catch (IOException e) {
            System.out.println("Error: " + e.getMessage());
        }
        // FileReader auto-closes because it implements AutoCloseable
    }
}